President Jacob Zuma was poisoned; foreign forces are trying to weaken the ANC; state capture is political propaganda and former Public Protector Thuli Madonsela's State of Capture Report was released for political reasons. These are some of the answers Zuma gave to ANN7 talk show host Sifiso Mahlangu during an interview with the formerly Gupta-owned broadcaster on Monday evening. The president has been media-shy since allegations of what is now known as state capture were made against him last year, most of which focused around his alleged corrupt relationship with the Gupta family and their associates. These are some of the eyebrow-raising statements he made on the show:      